{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Those are the dates we could make out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were gravestones there that were so damaged that one could not make out the exact date.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But 300-400 years is of a certainty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they not only lived in Oberwesel itself, which I think was a rather later development, they lived in the back country around this once walled city, and owned land, vineyards and grazing land, around Oberwesel.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the family, the Gerson family and their relatives, they were like clans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, they had many, many relatives.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because in many instances in the smaller towns, cousins married, since there were very few available Jewish females.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they married cousins, and sometimes first cousins, which has happened in the Gottschalks and the Gerson family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they kind of congregated, clustered around the smaller communities in which they lived, and would visit each other incessantly it seemed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was fortunate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had three sets of grandparents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother, who had her own set of parents, was adopted by her uncle and aunt after the Gersons, who are the uncle and aunt, lost their twin sons on the Russian front in World War I.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One was named Alfred, the other Berthold.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As it turns out, I'm named after one of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they approached my grandparents, the Trums in Gau-Odernheim, who were-- August Trum was the brother of Henrietta Wolff-Gerson.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she approached the grandparents, and asked whether they could have Erna come, my mother come, and live with them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother was one of five children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said, OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she lived with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They liked each other very much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then this became a permanent arrangement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They actually legally adopted her.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
